      {
        "front": "What is the primary function of Perimeter Security?",
        "back": "Perimeter Security protects the network boundary from external threats, acting as the first line of defense."
      },
      {
        "front": "How does Network Segmentation enhance security?",
        "back": "Network Segmentation enhances security by isolating different segments of the network, limiting the spread of potential threats."
      },
      {
        "front": "What is Threat Modeling?",
        "back": "Threat Modeling is the process of identifying potential threats to a system and understanding their impact."
      },
      {
        "front": "What role does Perimeter Security play in security architecture?",
        "back": "Perimeter Security serves as the first line of defense against external threats, crucial for maintaining network integrity."
      }
    ]
  }
}
